Metadata: UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA SEA GRANT COLLEGE PROGRAM ANNUAL REPORT 1973-1974
University of California Sea Grant, Institute of Marine Resources
program reports (annual, progress, planning reports, etc)
IMR Reference Number 75-1; Sea Grant Publication Number 41; NOAA-75051901

This is a report of activities for the University of California Sea Grant College Program for September 1, 1973, to August 31, 1974. Although our research efforts focus on wise utilization of marine resources, projects cover a great diversity of related subjects. There are social and legal studies related to coastal zone management, investigation of the aquaculture of various plants and animals, experimentation​ with new compounds derived from marine organisms, improvement of the marketability of canned tuna by improving canning processes, and development of a novel wave-protection system, to describe a few.
